Former Bosasa COO Angelo Agrizzi says he handed in his resignation in August 2016, because he was tired of fighting and had enough of working for CEO Gavin Watson. Agrizzi is testifying at the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture underway in Parktown, Johannesburg. He has told the Commission how things became shaky at the facility and management company during an investigation by the SIU. The unit was investigating Bosasa and the Department of Correctional Services and contracts the company received. Agrizzi says Watson was beginning to deny all wrong doing at the company saying he did not sign anything. Wrap of the day below:  The days full inquiry below: 